===Etymology===
Coined by Everett K Smith, President of the [[w:National Puzzlers' League|National Puzzlers’ League]], at their convention in 1935, from {{etyl|grc|en}} {{term|πνεύμων|tr=pneumōn||lung|lang=grc|sc=polytonic}} + {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|ultra||beyond|lang=la}} + {{etyl|en|-}} {{term|microscopic|lang=en}} + {{term|silico-|lang=en}} + {{term|volcano|lang=en}} + {{etyl|grc|en}} {{term|κόνις|tr=konis||dust|lang=grc|sc=polytonic}} + {{etyl|en|-}} {{term|-osis|lang=en}} as an extension of the medical term [[pneumonoconiosis]].

